Package zoot.tube.websocketserver

Class Server

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.java_websocket.WebSocketAdapter
      • org.java_websocket.AbstractWebSocket

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, org.java_websocket.WebSocketListener
    public class Server
extends org.java_websocket.server.WebSocketServer
    A web socket server that maintains only a single connection at a time. Only the newest connection is maintained, the previous connection will get closed.

      • addMessageHandler

        public void addMessageHandler​(java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.String> messageHandler)
        Adds a message handler.

        Note: Whenever this server receives a message, all message handlers are notified. So they should each check if the message is for them.

        Parameters:
        messageHandler - the message handler to add.

      • sendMessage

        public boolean sendMessage​(java.lang.String message)
        Sends a message to through the web socket.

        Note: This server only allows a single connection at a time, so the message will be sent only to the current connection.

        Parameters:
        message - the message to send.
        Returns:
        true if the message was sent, otherwise false.
